subSubSection.paragraph:
Hortophora walesiana

comb. nov. has been found mainly towards the coastal areas in the northern half of Australia, north of ca. 27°S Latitude in the Northern Territory, Queensland and Western Australia (Fig. 
32
). The holotype was collected at an unspecified location in New South Wales (
Karsch 1878
) and it can be assumed that the type locality, if not erroneously reported, was in the north-eastern part of that state.
